     5	/**
     6	 * An [ethers JsonRpcApiProvider](https://docs.ethers.org/v6/api/providers/jsonrpc/#JsonRpcApiProvider) using a tevm MemoryClient as it's backend
     7	 *
     8	 * ## TevmProvider
     9	 *
    10	 * The TevmProvider class is an instance of an ethers provider using Tevm as it's backend. The `createMemoryProvider` method can be used to create an in memory instance of tevm using a [memoryClient](../clients/) as it's backend.
    11	 *
    12	 * @example
    13	 * ```typescript
    14	 * import {TevmProvider} from '@tevm/ethers'
    15	 *
    16	 * const provider = await TevmProvider.createMemoryProvider({
    17	 *   fork: {
    18	 *     transport: http('https://mainnet.optimism.io')({}),
    19	 *   },
    20	 * })
    21	 * ```
    22	 *
    23	 * ## Using with an http client
    24	 *
    25	 * The constructor takes any instance of tevm including the `httpClient`.
    26	 *
    27	 * @example
    28	 * ```typescript
    29	 * import {createHttpClient} from '@tevm/http-client'
    30	 * const provider = new TevmProvider(createHttpClient({url: 'https://localhost:8080'}))
    31	 * ```
    32	 *
    33	 * ## Ethers provider support
    34	 *
    35	 * You can use all the normal ethers apis to interact with tevm.
    36	 *
    37	 * @example
    38	 * ```typescript
    39	 * const provider = await TevmProvider.createMemoryProvider({
    40	 *   fork: {
    41	 *     transport: http('https://mainnet.optimism.io')({}),
    42	 *   },
    43	 * })
    44	 *
    45	 * console.log(
    46	 *   await provider.getBlockNumber()
    47	 * ) // 10
    48	 * ```
    49	 *
    50	 * ## Tevm actions support
    51	 *
    52	 * The entire [tevm api](../clients/) exists on the `tevm` property. For example the `tevm.script` method can be used to run an arbitrary script.
    53	 *
    54	 * @example
    55	 * ```typescript
    56	 * import {TevmProvider} from '@tevm/ethers'
    57	 * import {createContract} from 'tevm'
    58	 *
    59	 * const provider = await TevmProvider.createMemoryProvider({
    60	 *   fork: {
    61	 *     transport: http('https://mainnet.optimism.io')({}),
    62	 *   },
    63	 * })
    64	 *
    65	 * const addContract = createContract({
    66	 *   name: 'AddContract',
    67	 *   humanReadableAbi: [
    68	 *     'function add(uint256 a, uint256 b) public pure returns (uint256)',
    69	 *   ],
    70	 *   deployedBytecode: '',
    71	 *   bytecode: '',
    72	 * } as const)
    73	 *
    74	 * const result = await provider.tevm.script(addContract.read.add(390n, 30n))
    75	 *
    76	 * console.log(result)
    77	 * //  createdAddresses: new Set(),
    78	 * //  data: 420n,
    79	 * //  executionGasUsed: 927n,
    80	 * //  gas: 16776288n,
    81	 * //  logs: [],
    82	 * //  rawData: '0x00000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000001a4',
    83	 * //  selfdestruct: new Set(),
    84	 * ```
    85	 *
    86	 * ## Tevm JSON-RPC support
    87	 *
    88	 * An ethers TevmProvider supports the tevm [JSON-RPC methods](../json-rpc). For example you can use `tevm_account` to set account
    89	 *
    90	 * @example
    91	 * ```typescript
